{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1773740284219_2rom8ib3eo","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-4.7","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_19a0a0bb1414406f8fc730c0","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/context-snapshot.md","content":"# Context Snapshot: F-015 - AI CLI Backend Switcher\n\n## Section 1: Feature Brief\n\n**Feature ID**: F-015\n**Feature Slug**: 015-ai-cli-backend-switcher\n**Session**: F-015-20260317173631\n\n### Feature Description\n通过 /cli 命令动态切换 AI 后端，无需重启 Bot。当前系统硬编码使用 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置的单一后端，用户无法在运行时切换到其他 AI CLI（如 claude-internal、claude、cbc 等）。\n\n### Commands Design\n- `/cli` - 查看当前使用的 AI 后端名称和路径\n- `/cli <backend>` - 切换到指定后端（如 /cli claude-internal），切换后当前会话立即使用新后端执行后续对话\n- `/cli list` - 列出所有可用的后端\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- /cli 返回当前会话使用的 AI 后端名称与 bin 路径\n- /cli <backend> 切换后端，切换后下一条消息立即使用新后端\n- /cli list 列出所有已配置的可用后端\n- 切换前自动检测目标后端二进制是否存在，不存在时拒绝并提示\n- 每个会话独立维护后端选择，不同用户可以使用不同后端\n- Bot 重启后恢复为默认后端（CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置值）\n\n### Dependencies (Already Completed)\n- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed)\n- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2: Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n│   └── codebuddy.js                    # Web端 chat adapter\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── handlers/                   # Command handlers (one file per command)\n│   │   │   ├── status.js\n│   │   │   ├── alias.js\n│   │   │   └── ...\n│   │   ├── registry.js                 # Command registration\n│   │   └── index.js\n│   └── telegram.js                     # Telegram bot entry point\n├── services/\n│   ├── ai-cli-service.js               # AI CLI execution service (F-011)\n│   ├── session-store.js                # In-memory session storage\n│   ├── session-context-service.js      # Session persistence (F-013)\n│   └── chat-service.js                 # Web chat service\n├── routes/\n│   └── api-routes.js\n├── config.js                           # Configuration with Zod validation\n└── index.js\ntests/\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   └── handlers/                   # Handler tests\n│   └── commands/\n└── helpers/                            # Test helpers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3: Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm\n```\nPRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (Node.js ES modules)\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram to AI CLI bridge - sends commands from Telegram to CodeBuddy/Claude CLI, streams output back\nENTRY_POINT: src/index.js\n\nTECH_STACK:\n- runtime: Node.js (ES modules, --watch for dev)\n- bot: Telegraf 4.x (Telegram Bot API)\n- http: Express 4.x\n- validation: Zod\n- logging: Pino\n- config: dotenv\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src.prizm\n- dev-pipeline -> .prizm-docs/dev-pipeline.prizm\n\nRULES:\n- All source is ESM (import/export, \"type\": \"module\")\n- Config via Zod schema validation from .env\n- Security: permission-guard, system-guard, param-sanitizer, confirmation-manager\n- Tests use Node.js built-in test runner (node --test)\n- Conventional Commits format required\n- POSIX shell commands preferred\n\nPATTERNS:\n- Service layer pattern: src/services/ contains business logic\n- Command handler pattern: src/bot/commands/handlers/ one file per command\n- Registry pattern: commands registered in src/bot/commands/registry.js\n- Barrel exports: index.js files re-export module contents\n```\n\n### src.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src\nFILES: index.js, config.js\nRESPONSIBILITY: Main application - Telegram bot bridge to AI CLI with web dashboard\n\nSUBDIRS:\n- bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n\nINTERFACES:\n- config: validated env config object (Zod schema)\n- createTelegramBot(): Telegraf bot instance\n- createHttpServer(): Express app\n```\n\n### src/bot.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src/bot\nFILES: telegram.js, commands/index.js, commands/registry.js, commands/...\nRESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot setup and command routing system\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- telegram.js: bot creation, middleware setup, message handling\n- commands/registry.js: command registration and lookup\n\nINTERFACES:\n- createTelegramBot(): creates and configures Telegraf bot\n- CommandRegistry: register/lookup/list commands\n```\n\n### src/services.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src/services\nFILES: index.js, ai-cli-service.js, session-store.js, session-context-service.js, chat-service.js, ...\nRESPONSIBILITY: Business logic layer - all domain services\n\nINTERFACES:\n- AiCliService: spawn and manage AI CLI sessions, stream output\n- SessionStore: manage active CLI sessions\n- executeAiCli({ sessionId, prompt, bin, ... }): main execution function\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4: Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js (Key configs)\n```javascript\n// Schema includes:\nCODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\nCODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n\n// Exported config:\ncodebuddyBin: parsed.CODEBUDDY_BIN,\ncodebuddyPermissionFlag: parsed.CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG,\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // ... other storage Maps\n\n  clear(sessionKey) {\n    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // ... clears all Maps\n  }\n\n  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) {\n    // Returns comprehensive session info\n    return { sessionKey, userId, cwd, envOverrides, ... };\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/ai-cli-service.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n * @property {string} bin - Optional binary override (for testing)\n */\n\nexport async function executeAiCli(options) {\n  const { bin, prompt, sessionId, ... } = options;\n\n  const effectiveBin = bin || config.codebuddyBin;  // Hard-coded to config\n\n  const child = spawn(effectiveBin, args, { stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });\n  // ... process handling\n}\n```\n\n### src/adapters/codebuddy.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\nexport async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n  }\n\n  const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n    stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n  });\n  // ... process handling\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/registry.js\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} CommandMeta\n * @property {string} name\n * @property {string[]} [aliases]\n * @property {string} description\n * @property {string} usage\n * @property {string[]} examples\n * @property {boolean} requiresAuth\n * @property {string} minRole\n */\n\nexport function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n  // Registers command with metadata and handler\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (Key patterns)\n```javascript\n// Command registration pattern\nfunction registerPipelineCommands() {\n  registerCommand(pipelineMeta, handlePipeline);\n  registerCommand(aliasMeta, handleAlias);\n  // ... more commands\n}\n\n// Text message handling (line 827-994)\nbot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n  // Checks if AI CLI is running\n  if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n    await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Executes AI CLI\n  const result = await executeAiCli({\n    sessionId,\n    prompt,\n    hooks: { onChunk, onHeartbeat, onStatus }\n  });\n});\n\n// Session key pattern: `telegram:${sessionId}`\nconst sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5: Existing Tests\n\n### tests/helpers/helpers.test.js\nShows test helper patterns:\n- `createMockContext()` - Creates mock Telegram context with `reply()` capture\n- `ctx._getReplies()` - Gets captured replies\n- `ctx._getLastReply()` - Gets last reply\n\n### Handler test pattern (from commands/handlers/status.js)\n```javascript\nexport async function handleStatus(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, params, ctx, userId } = handlerCtx;\n  // ... implementation\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Context\n\n### Key Integration Points\n\n1. **SessionStore** - Need to add storage for per-session AI backend choice\n   - Add `#aiBackendBySessionKey` Map\n   - Add `getAiBackend(sessionKey)` and `setAiBackend(sessionKey, backend)`\n   - Update `clear()` to include backend clearing\n\n2. **AiCliService** - `executeAiCli()` already accepts optional `bin` parameter\n   - Currently falls back to `config.codebuddyBin`\n   - Need to pass session's selected backend\n\n3. **Telegram Bot** - Need new `/cli` command handler\n   - Register `cliMeta` and `handleCli`\n   - No parameter: show current backend\n   - Parameter: switch to backend with validation\n   - \"list\" subcommand: show available backends\n\n4. **Web Chat** - `chat-service.js` uses `runCodeBuddy` from `codebuddy.js`\n   - Need to make `runCodeBuddy` accept optional `bin` parameter\n   - Pass session's selected backend\n\n5. **Config** - Add new config for available backends\n   - `AI_BACKENDS` env var: comma-separated list of backend names\n   - `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH` pattern: path for each backend\n   - Fallback to common paths if not configured\n\n### Design Decisions Needed\n\n1. **Backend Configuration Format**\n   - Option A: Single `AI_BACKENDS` env with key=value pairs\n   - Option B: Multiple `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH` env vars\n   - Option C: JSON config file\n\n2. **Default Backend Selection**\n   - Use first configured backend\n   - Or use `CODEBUDDY_BIN` as default\n\n3. **Web Session Backend Management**\n   - Add `/api/cli` endpoint to get/set backend\n   - Store per sessionId in sessionStore\n\n### Files to Create/Modify\n\n**Create:**\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js` - /cli command handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cli.test.js` - Tests\n\n**Modify:**\n- `src/services/session-store.js` - Add backend storage methods\n- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Register /cli command, pass backend to executeAiCli\n- `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` - Accept optional `bin` parameter\n- `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add /api/cli routes (for web)\n- `src/config.js` - Add backend config schema\n"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":74178,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c8ebc62-648e-4d09-8200-69d30faee4f6","uuid":"b6be28ed-bbae-44b1-a2de-31bff0b8e07f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_19a0a0bb1414406f8fc730c0","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/context-snapshot.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c8ebc62-648e-4d09-8200-69d30faee4f6","uuid":"70dcebcc-6f5c-4947-a9b8-6a7ff714ac2f","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/context-snapshot.md","content":"# Context Snapshot: F-015 - AI CLI Backend Switcher\n\n## Section 1: Feature Brief\n\n**Feature ID**: F-015\n**Feature Slug**: 015-ai-cli-backend-switcher\n**Session**: F-015-20260317173631\n\n### Feature Description\n通过 /cli 命令动态切换 AI 后端，无需重启 Bot。当前系统硬编码使用 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置的单一后端，用户无法在运行时切换到其他 AI CLI（如 claude-internal、claude、cbc 等）。\n\n### Commands Design\n- `/cli` - 查看当前使用的 AI 后端名称和路径\n- `/cli <backend>` - 切换到指定后端（如 /cli claude-internal），切换后当前会话立即使用新后端执行后续对话\n- `/cli list` - 列出所有可用的后端\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- /cli 返回当前会话使用的 AI 后端名称与 bin 路径\n- /cli <backend> 切换后端，切换后下一条消息立即使用新后端\n- /cli list 列出所有已配置的可用后端\n- 切换前自动检测目标后端二进制是否存在，不存在时拒绝并提示\n- 每个会话独立维护后端选择，不同用户可以使用不同后端\n- Bot 重启后恢复为默认后端（CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置值）\n\n### Dependencies (Already Completed)\n- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed)\n- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2: Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/\n│   └── codebuddy.js                    # Web端 chat adapter\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   ├── handlers/                   # Command handlers (one file per command)\n│   │   │   ├── status.js\n│   │   │   ├── alias.js\n│   │   │   └── ...\n│   │   ├── registry.js                 # Command registration\n│   │   └── index.js\n│   └── telegram.js                     # Telegram bot entry point\n├── services/\n│   ├── ai-cli-service.js               # AI CLI execution service (F-011)\n│   ├── session-store.js                # In-memory session storage\n│   ├── session-context-service.js      # Session persistence (F-013)\n│   └── chat-service.js                 # Web chat service\n├── routes/\n│   └── api-routes.js\n├── config.js                           # Configuration with Zod validation\n└── index.js\ntests/\n├── bot/\n│   ├── commands/\n│   │   └── handlers/                   # Handler tests\n│   └── commands/\n└── helpers/                            # Test helpers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3: Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm\n```\nPRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (Node.js ES modules)\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram to AI CLI bridge - sends commands from Telegram to CodeBuddy/Claude CLI, streams output back\nENTRY_POINT: src/index.js\n\nTECH_STACK:\n- runtime: Node.js (ES modules, --watch for dev)\n- bot: Telegraf 4.x (Telegram Bot API)\n- http: Express 4.x\n- validation: Zod\n- logging: Pino\n- config: dotenv\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src.prizm\n- dev-pipeline -> .prizm-docs/dev-pipeline.prizm\n\nRULES:\n- All source is ESM (import/export, \"type\": \"module\")\n- Config via Zod schema validation from .env\n- Security: permission-guard, system-guard, param-sanitizer, confirmation-manager\n- Tests use Node.js built-in test runner (node --test)\n- Conventional Commits format required\n- POSIX shell commands preferred\n\nPATTERNS:\n- Service layer pattern: src/services/ contains business logic\n- Command handler pattern: src/bot/commands/handlers/ one file per command\n- Registry pattern: commands registered in src/bot/commands/registry.js\n- Barrel exports: index.js files re-export module contents\n```\n\n### src.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src\nFILES: index.js, config.js\nRESPONSIBILITY: Main application - Telegram bot bridge to AI CLI with web dashboard\n\nSUBDIRS:\n- bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n\nINTERFACES:\n- config: validated env config object (Zod schema)\n- createTelegramBot(): Telegraf bot instance\n- createHttpServer(): Express app\n```\n\n### src/bot.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src/bot\nFILES: telegram.js, commands/index.js, commands/registry.js, commands/...\nRESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot setup and command routing system\n\nKEY_FILES:\n- telegram.js: bot creation, middleware setup, message handling\n- commands/registry.js: command registration and lookup\n\nINTERFACES:\n- createTelegramBot(): creates and configures Telegraf bot\n- CommandRegistry: register/lookup/list commands\n```\n\n### src/services.prizm\n```\nMODULE: src/services\nFILES: index.js, ai-cli-service.js, session-store.js, session-context-service.js, chat-service.js, ...\nRESPONSIBILITY: Business logic layer - all domain services\n\nINTERFACES:\n- AiCliService: spawn and manage AI CLI sessions, stream output\n- SessionStore: manage active CLI sessions\n- executeAiCli({ sessionId, prompt, bin, ... }): main execution function\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4: Existing Source Files\n\n### src/config.js (Key configs)\n```javascript\n// Schema includes:\nCODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\nCODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n\n// Exported config:\ncodebuddyBin: parsed.CODEBUDDY_BIN,\ncodebuddyPermissionFlag: parsed.CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG,\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // ... other storage Maps\n\n  clear(sessionKey) {\n    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // ... clears all Maps\n  }\n\n  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) {\n    // Returns comprehensive session info\n    return { sessionKey, userId, cwd, envOverrides, ... };\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/ai-cli-service.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n * @property {string} bin - Optional binary override (for testing)\n */\n\nexport async function executeAiCli(options) {\n  const { bin, prompt, sessionId, ... } = options;\n\n  const effectiveBin = bin || config.codebuddyBin;  // Hard-coded to config\n\n  const child = spawn(effectiveBin, args, { stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });\n  // ... process handling\n}\n```\n\n### src/adapters/codebuddy.js (Key parts)\n```javascript\nexport async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n  }\n\n  const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n    stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n  });\n  // ... process handling\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/registry.js\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} CommandMeta\n * @property {string} name\n * @property {string[]} [aliases]\n * @property {string} description\n * @property {string} usage\n * @property {string[]} examples\n * @property {boolean} requiresAuth\n * @property {string} minRole\n */\n\nexport function registerCommand(meta, handler) {\n  // Registers command with metadata and handler\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (Key patterns)\n```javascript\n// Command registration pattern\nfunction registerPipelineCommands() {\n  registerCommand(pipelineMeta, handlePipeline);\n  registerCommand(aliasMeta, handleAlias);\n  // ... more commands\n}\n\n// Text message handling (line 827-994)\nbot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n  // Checks if AI CLI is running\n  if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n    await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Executes AI CLI\n  const result = await executeAiCli({\n    sessionId,\n    prompt,\n    hooks: { onChunk, onHeartbeat, onStatus }\n  });\n});\n\n// Session key pattern: `telegram:${sessionId}`\nconst sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5: Existing Tests\n\n### tests/helpers/helpers.test.js\nShows test helper patterns:\n- `createMockContext()` - Creates mock Telegram context with `reply()` capture\n- `ctx._getReplies()` - Gets captured replies\n- `ctx._getLastReply()` - Gets last reply\n\n### Handler test pattern (from commands/handlers/status.js)\n```javascript\nexport async function handleStatus(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, params, ctx, userId } = handlerCtx;\n  // ... implementation\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Context\n\n### Key Integration Points\n\n1. **SessionStore** - Need to add storage for per-session AI backend choice\n   - Add `#aiBackendBySessionKey` Map\n   - Add `getAiBackend(sessionKey)` and `setAiBackend(sessionKey, backend)`\n   - Update `clear()` to include backend clearing\n\n2. **AiCliService** - `executeAiCli()` already accepts optional `bin` parameter\n   - Currently falls back to `config.codebuddyBin`\n   - Need to pass session's selected backend\n\n3. **Telegram Bot** - Need new `/cli` command handler\n   - Register `cliMeta` and `handleCli`\n   - No parameter: show current backend\n   - Parameter: switch to backend with validation\n   - \"list\" subcommand: show available backends\n\n4. **Web Chat** - `chat-service.js` uses `runCodeBuddy` from `codebuddy.js`\n   - Need to make `runCodeBuddy` accept optional `bin` parameter\n   - Pass session's selected backend\n\n5. **Config** - Add new config for available backends\n   - `AI_BACKENDS` env var: comma-separated list of backend names\n   - `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH` pattern: path for each backend\n   - Fallback to common paths if not configured\n\n### Design Decisions Needed\n\n1. **Backend Configuration Format**\n   - Option A: Single `AI_BACKENDS` env with key=value pairs\n   - Option B: Multiple `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH` env vars\n   - Option C: JSON config file\n\n2. **Default Backend Selection**\n   - Use first configured backend\n   - Or use `CODEBUDDY_BIN` as default\n\n3. **Web Session Backend Management**\n   - Add `/api/cli` endpoint to get/set backend\n   - Store per sessionId in sessionStore\n\n### Files to Create/Modify\n\n**Create:**\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js` - /cli command handler\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cli.test.js` - Tests\n\n**Modify:**\n- `src/services/session-store.js` - Add backend storage methods\n- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Register /cli command, pass backend to executeAiCli\n- `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` - Accept optional `bin` parameter\n- `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add /api/cli routes (for web)\n- `src/config.js` - Add backend config schema\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1773740381161_2jm2z6upykn","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-4.7","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_fbf28bce93024290b106dcc1","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/plan.md","content":"# Plan: F-015 - AI CLI Backend Switcher\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **Backend Configuration** (config.js)\n   - New config schema for available AI backends\n   - `AI_BACKENDS`: Comma-separated backend names (e.g., \"claude-internal,claude,codebuddy\")\n   - `AI_BACKEND_DEFAULT`: Default backend name\n   - Automatic path resolution for each backend\n\n2. **Session Backend Storage** (session-store.js)\n   - `#aiBackendBySessionKey` Map for per-session backend choice\n   - `getAiBackend(sessionKey)` - Get session's backend or default\n   - `setAiBackend(sessionKey, backend)` - Set session's backend\n   - Extended in `clear()` and `getSessionInfo()`\n\n3. **Backend Resolution Service** (new: src/services/backend-resolver.js)\n   - `resolveBackend(backendName)` - Get bin path for backend name\n   - `ensureBinaryAvailable(binPath)` - Check if binary exists\n   - `listAvailableBackends()` - List all configured backends with availability\n   - `getDefaultBackend()` - Get configured default\n\n4. **CLI Command Handler** (new: src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js)\n   - `/cli [backend]` - Show current or switch backend\n   - `/cli list` - List all backends\n   - Validates backend exists before switching\n   - Error messages in Chinese for Telegram\n\n5. **Adapters Update** (adapters/codebuddy.js)\n   - `runCodeBuddy(prompt, { bin, ... })` - Accept optional `bin` parameter\n\n6. **Web API Routes** (routes/api-routes.js)\n   - `GET /api/cli` - Get current backend for session\n   - `POST /api/cli` - Set backend for session\n   - `GET /api/cli/list` - List all available backends\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nUser sends /cli claude-internal\n    ↓\nhandleCli() validates backend\n    ↓\nbackendResolver.ensureBinaryAvailable()\n    ↓\nsessionStore.setAiBackend(sessionKey, 'claude-internal')\n    ↓\nNext message: telegram on('text')\n    ↓\nexecuteAiCli({\n  sessionId,\n  prompt,\n  bin: sessionStore.getAiBackend(sessionKey)  <-- Uses session backend\n})\n```\n\n### Interface Contracts\n\n#### sessionStore extensions\n```javascript\ngetAiBackend(sessionKey): string | null  // Returns backend name or null\nsetAiBackend(sessionKey, backend): void  // Stores backend name\n```\n\n#### backendResolver\n```javascript\nresolveBackend(backendName): string | Error  // Returns bin path or throws\nensureBinaryAvailable(binPath): boolean     // Returns true if exists\nlistAvailableBackends(): Array<{name, path, available}>\ngetDefaultBackend(): string                 // Default backend name\n```\n\n### Files to Create\n\n1. `src/services/backend-resolver.js` - Backend resolution and validation\n2. `src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js` - /cli command handler\n3. `tests/services/backend-resolver.test.js` - Resolver tests\n4. `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cli.test.js` - Handler tests\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n1. `src/config.js` - Add backend config schema\n2. `src/services/session-store.js` - Add backend storage\n3. `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` - Accept `bin` parameter\n4. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Register command, pass backend\n5. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add API routes\n6. `src/services/session-context-service.js` - Persist backend choice\n\n## Config Design\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```\n# Comma-separated list of backend names\nAI_BACKENDS=claude-internal,claude,codebuddy,cbc\n\n# Default backend (optional, defaults to first)\nAI_BACKEND_DEFAULT=claude-internal\n\n# Optional: explicit paths for each backend (auto-resolved if not set)\nAI_BACKEND_CLAUDE_INTERNAL_PATH=/usr/local/bin/claude-internal\nAI_BACKEND_CLAUDE_PATH=/usr/local/bin/claude\n```\n\n### Default Path Resolution\n\nFor each backend name, try these paths:\n1. Env override: `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH`\n2. Direct name: `codebuddy`, `claude`, etc.\n3. Common paths:\n   - `/usr/local/bin/{name}`\n   - `/usr/bin/{name}`\n   - `~/.local/bin/{name}`\n\n## Testing Approach\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **backend-resolver.test.js**\n   - resolveBackend() returns correct path\n   - resolveBackend() throws for unknown backend\n   - ensureBinaryAvailable() returns true/false correctly\n   - listAvailableBackends() returns availability status\n\n2. **session-store extensions**\n   - Test getter/setter for AI backend\n   - Test clear() removes backend\n\n3. **cli.test.js**\n   - /cli with no args shows current backend\n   - /cli switches backend successfully\n   - /cli rejects non-existent backend\n   - /cli list shows all backends\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. Telegram message flow with backend switch\n2. Web API get/set backend endpoint\n3. Session persistence across bot restart\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n1. Session has no backend set → use default\n2. Backend binary removed → show as unavailable\n3. Switch while AI CLI running → allow (affects next message)\n4. Invalid backend name → clear error message\n5. All backends unavailable → show error, don't break startup\n"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":77195,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c8ebc62-648e-4d09-8200-69d30faee4f6","uuid":"c56e6d48-f42e-4251-a197-565cb99820dd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_fbf28bce93024290b106dcc1","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/plan.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c8ebc62-648e-4d09-8200-69d30faee4f6","uuid":"df403d69-6e57-4f1a-baca-f0bedd5f8bd7","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/plan.md","content":"# Plan: F-015 - AI CLI Backend Switcher\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **Backend Configuration** (config.js)\n   - New config schema for available AI backends\n   - `AI_BACKENDS`: Comma-separated backend names (e.g., \"claude-internal,claude,codebuddy\")\n   - `AI_BACKEND_DEFAULT`: Default backend name\n   - Automatic path resolution for each backend\n\n2. **Session Backend Storage** (session-store.js)\n   - `#aiBackendBySessionKey` Map for per-session backend choice\n   - `getAiBackend(sessionKey)` - Get session's backend or default\n   - `setAiBackend(sessionKey, backend)` - Set session's backend\n   - Extended in `clear()` and `getSessionInfo()`\n\n3. **Backend Resolution Service** (new: src/services/backend-resolver.js)\n   - `resolveBackend(backendName)` - Get bin path for backend name\n   - `ensureBinaryAvailable(binPath)` - Check if binary exists\n   - `listAvailableBackends()` - List all configured backends with availability\n   - `getDefaultBackend()` - Get configured default\n\n4. **CLI Command Handler** (new: src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js)\n   - `/cli [backend]` - Show current or switch backend\n   - `/cli list` - List all backends\n   - Validates backend exists before switching\n   - Error messages in Chinese for Telegram\n\n5. **Adapters Update** (adapters/codebuddy.js)\n   - `runCodeBuddy(prompt, { bin, ... })` - Accept optional `bin` parameter\n\n6. **Web API Routes** (routes/api-routes.js)\n   - `GET /api/cli` - Get current backend for session\n   - `POST /api/cli` - Set backend for session\n   - `GET /api/cli/list` - List all available backends\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nUser sends /cli claude-internal\n    ↓\nhandleCli() validates backend\n    ↓\nbackendResolver.ensureBinaryAvailable()\n    ↓\nsessionStore.setAiBackend(sessionKey, 'claude-internal')\n    ↓\nNext message: telegram on('text')\n    ↓\nexecuteAiCli({\n  sessionId,\n  prompt,\n  bin: sessionStore.getAiBackend(sessionKey)  <-- Uses session backend\n})\n```\n\n### Interface Contracts\n\n#### sessionStore extensions\n```javascript\ngetAiBackend(sessionKey): string | null  // Returns backend name or null\nsetAiBackend(sessionKey, backend): void  // Stores backend name\n```\n\n#### backendResolver\n```javascript\nresolveBackend(backendName): string | Error  // Returns bin path or throws\nensureBinaryAvailable(binPath): boolean     // Returns true if exists\nlistAvailableBackends(): Array<{name, path, available}>\ngetDefaultBackend(): string                 // Default backend name\n```\n\n### Files to Create\n\n1. `src/services/backend-resolver.js` - Backend resolution and validation\n2. `src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js` - /cli command handler\n3. `tests/services/backend-resolver.test.js` - Resolver tests\n4. `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cli.test.js` - Handler tests\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n1. `src/config.js` - Add backend config schema\n2. `src/services/session-store.js` - Add backend storage\n3. `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` - Accept `bin` parameter\n4. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Register command, pass backend\n5. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add API routes\n6. `src/services/session-context-service.js` - Persist backend choice\n\n## Config Design\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```\n# Comma-separated list of backend names\nAI_BACKENDS=claude-internal,claude,codebuddy,cbc\n\n# Default backend (optional, defaults to first)\nAI_BACKEND_DEFAULT=claude-internal\n\n# Optional: explicit paths for each backend (auto-resolved if not set)\nAI_BACKEND_CLAUDE_INTERNAL_PATH=/usr/local/bin/claude-internal\nAI_BACKEND_CLAUDE_PATH=/usr/local/bin/claude\n```\n\n### Default Path Resolution\n\nFor each backend name, try these paths:\n1. Env override: `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH`\n2. Direct name: `codebuddy`, `claude`, etc.\n3. Common paths:\n   - `/usr/local/bin/{name}`\n   - `/usr/bin/{name}`\n   - `~/.local/bin/{name}`\n\n## Testing Approach\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **backend-resolver.test.js**\n   - resolveBackend() returns correct path\n   - resolveBackend() throws for unknown backend\n   - ensureBinaryAvailable() returns true/false correctly\n   - listAvailableBackends() returns availability status\n\n2. **session-store extensions**\n   - Test getter/setter for AI backend\n   - Test clear() removes backend\n\n3. **cli.test.js**\n   - /cli with no args shows current backend\n   - /cli switches backend successfully\n   - /cli rejects non-existent backend\n   - /cli list shows all backends\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. Telegram message flow with backend switch\n2. Web API get/set backend endpoint\n3. Session persistence across bot restart\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n1. Session has no backend set → use default\n2. Backend binary removed → show as unavailable\n3. Switch while AI CLI running → allow (affects next message)\n4. Invalid backend name → clear error message\n5. All backends unavailable → show error, don't break startup\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_1773740438889_np7z29kz7r","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-4.7","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_fea92d8845444423973e584e","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/015-ai-cli-backend-switcher/tasks.md","content":"# Tasks: F-015 - AI CLI Backend Switcher\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **T1**: Add backend config schema to `src/config.js`\n  - Add `AI_BACKENDS` env var (comma-separated list)\n  - Add `AI_BACKEND_DEFAULT` env var\n  - Add path override pattern `AI_BACKEND_<NAME>_PATH`\n  - Export `aiBackends` and `aiBackendDefault` in config\n\n- [ ] **T2**: Create `src/services/backend-resolver.js`\n  - Implement `resolveBackend(backendName)` with path resolution\n  - Implement `ensureBinaryAvailable(binPath)` using `which` or `command -v`\n  - Implement `listAvailableBackends()` with availability check\n  - Implement `getDefaultBackend()` returning configured default\n  - Mock `which` calls for testing\n\n- [ ] **T3**: Add AI backend tests for `tests/runtime/config.test.js`\n  - Test AI_BACKENDS parsing\n  - Test AI_BACKEND_DEFAULT parsing\n  - Test path override format\n\n- [ ] **T4**: Create `tests/services/backend-resolver.test.js`\n  - Test resolveBackend() with valid name\n  - Test resolveBackend() throws for unknown name\n  - Test ensureBinaryAvailable() with mocked which\n  - Test listAvailableBackends() returns correct availability\n  - Test getDefaultBackend() returns configured or first\n\n### Phase 2: Session Storage\n\n- [ ] **T5**: Add backend storage to `src/services/session-store.js`\n  - Add `#aiBackendBySessionKey` Map\n  - Implement `getAiBackend(sessionKey)`\n  - Implement `setAiBackend(sessionKey, backend)`\n  - Update `clear()` to remove backend\n  - Extend `getSessionInfo()` to include backend\n\n- [ ] **T6**: Add session-store backend tests\n  - Test getAiBackend() returns null for new session\n  - Test setAiBackend() followed by getAiBackend()\n  - Test clear() removes backend\n  - Test getSessionInfo() includes backend\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Command Handler\n\n- [ ] **T7**: Create `src/bot/commands/handlers/cli.js`\n  - Define cliMeta with description, usage, examples\n  - Implement handleCli() with subcommand parsing\n  - No args: show current backend with path\n  - \"list\" subcommand: show all available backends\n  - Backend name: validate, switch, confirm\n\n- [ ] **T8**: Register /cli command in `src/bot/telegram.js`\n  - Import cliMeta and handleCli\n  - Add registerCommand(cliMeta, handleCli) in registerPipelineCommands()\n\n- [ ] **T9**: Create `tests/bot/commands/handlers/cli.test.js`\n  - Test /cli shows current backend\n  - Test /cli list shows all backends\n  - Test /cli <backend> switches successfully\n  - Test /cli <invalid-backend> shows error\n  - Test /cli <unavailable-backend> shows unavailable message\n\n### Phase 4: AI CLI Integration\n\n- [ ] **T10**: Update `src/bot/telegram.js` to use session backend\n  - In bot.on('text'), get backend from sessionStore\n  - Pass `bin` to executeAiCli() if session has backend\n  - Use backendResolver.resolveBackend() to get path\n\n- [ ] **T11**: Update `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` for web support\n  - Accept optional `bin` parameter in runCodeBuddy()\n  - Use passed bin or fall back to config.codebuddyBin\n  - Update logging to show actual bin used\n\n- [ ] **T12**: Add Web API routes to `src/routes/api-routes.js`\n  - GET /api/cli?sessionId=X - get current backend\n  - POST /api/cli with {sessionId, backend} - set backend\n  - GET /api/cli/list - list all backends\n\n- [ ] **T13**: Update `src/services/session-context-service.js`\n  - Add aiBackend to persistSession() data\n  - Restore aiBackend in restoreSessions()\n  - Ensure backend is cleared on session cleanup\n\n### Phase 5: Final Testing & Documentation\n\n- [ ] **T14**: Integration test - Telegram backend switch flow\n  - Create test showing backend stored in session\n  - Switch backend and verify next execution uses new one\n  - Test session cleanup clears backend\n\n- [ ] **T15**: Integration test - Web API backend endpoints\n  - Test GET /api/cli returns default initially\n  - Test POST /api/cli sets backend\n  - Test GET /api/cli/list returns all backends\n\n- [ ] **T16**: Run existing test suite to verify no regressions\n  - Run all tests with `node --test`\n  - Verify no breaking changes to existing functionality\n\n- [ ] **T17**: Manual acceptance testing\n  - Test /cli command in Telegram\n  - Test switching backends mid-conversation\n  - Verify bot restart resets to default backend\n  - Test all acceptance criteria\n\n---\n\n## Order of Execution\n\n```\nT1 → T2 → T3 → T4 (Infrastructure + Resolver)\n    ↓\nT5 → T6 (Session Storage)\n    ↓\nT7 → T8 → T9 (CLI Command)\n    ↓\nT10 → T11 → T12 → T13 (Integration)\n    ↓\nT14 → T15 → T16 → T17 (Testing)\n```\n"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":78538,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c8ebc62-648e-4d09-8200-69d30faee4f6","uuid":"2d1ad92d-1a46-4e31-afc8-d4175af61e66"}
